WEBVTT

1
00:01:50.880 --> 00:01:53.600
(CLANGING)

2
00:01:54.840 --> 00:01:56.760
(PEOPLE CHATTING)

3
00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:11.840
(LAUGHS)
Here we are.

4
00:02:15.760 --> 00:02:18.880
(LAUGHTER. LOUD CHATTER)

5
00:02:19.040 --> 00:02:20.720
Ready?

6
00:02:24.080 --> 00:02:26.160
(BELCHING)

7
00:02:26.320 --> 00:02:28.000
"The Rains of Castamere."

8
00:02:28.160 --> 00:02:29.800
You fucking deaf?
(LAUGHING)

9
00:02:29.960 --> 00:02:32.280
Same wrong guess every fucking time.

10
00:02:32.440 --> 00:02:35.800
-Listen. you cunt.
-MEN: Oh!

11
00:02:35.960 --> 00:02:38.520
(BELCHING)

12
00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:42.120
"The Bear and the Maiden Fair."
(CHEERING)

13
00:02:42.280 --> 00:02:43.960
There's a man with an ear.

14
00:02:44.120 --> 00:02:46.120
Too bad you got a hangnail for a cock.

15
00:02:46.280 --> 00:02:48.280
(LAUGHS)

16
00:02:48.440 --> 00:02:50.120
First time I saw you
with your breeches down.

17
00:02:50.280 --> 00:02:52.760
I thought you were a eunuch.
(ALL LAUGHING)

18
00:02:52.920 --> 00:02:58.480
You've seen it. girls. Like
a baby snail peeking out of his shell.

19
00:02:58.640 --> 00:03:01.120
(LAUGHS)

20
00:03:10.800 --> 00:03:13.040
Your baby was crying this morning.

21
00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:20.120
Woke me up.

22
00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:23.600
-You hear me?
-Yes.

23
00:03:23.760 --> 00:03:26.080
Well. got anything to say?

24
00:03:26.240 --> 00:03:27.880
I'm sorry he woke you up.

25
00:03:28.040 --> 00:03:31.800
(CHUCKLES)
I don't care if you're sorry.

26
00:03:31.960 --> 00:03:33.720
Keep that baby quiet

27
00:03:33.880 --> 00:03:35.200
or I will.

28
00:03:35.360 --> 00:03:36.960
Don't you ever touch him.

29
00:03:37.120 --> 00:03:38.640
(CHUCKLES)

30
00:03:38.800 --> 00:03:41.760
Little wildling bitch.

31
00:03:41.920 --> 00:03:44.000
You should have stayed
with your own kind.

32
00:03:44.160 --> 00:03:46.320
(OWL HOOTS)

33
00:03:46.480 --> 00:03:48.640
-You listening to me?
-Shut your mouth.

34
00:03:48.800 --> 00:03:52.280
What?
(OWL HOOTS)

35
00:03:52.440 --> 00:03:54.240
It's just an owl. you dumb bitch.

36
00:03:54.400 --> 00:03:56.440
No. it's not.

37
00:04:04.760 --> 00:04:07.000
(OWL HOOTS)

38
00:04:14.560 --> 00:04:16.800
(KNIFE CUT)

39
00:04:23.640 --> 00:04:25.840
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

40
00:04:28.640 --> 00:04:30.560
(GRUNTS)

41
00:04:38.440 --> 00:04:40.560
(WOMEN SCREAMING)

42
00:04:57.720 --> 00:05:00.440
(SHOUTING)

43
00:05:00.600 --> 00:05:03.160
(GRUNTS)

44
00:05:03.320 --> 00:05:06.320
(GURGLES)

45
00:05:06.480 --> 00:05:08.880
(BOTTLES RATTLE)

46
00:05:09.040 --> 00:05:11.280
(SCREAMS)

47
00:05:14.800 --> 00:05:17.640
(BABY FUSSES)

48
00:05:29.880 --> 00:05:33.360
(BABY FUSSES)
Shh.

49
00:05:33.520 --> 00:05:35.880
(LIQUID POURING)

50
00:05:36.040 --> 00:05:38.160
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

51
00:05:40.160 --> 00:05:42.360
I should never have left her there.

52
00:05:42.520 --> 00:05:45.800
-You couldn't have known.
-Of course I could've known.

53
00:05:45.960 --> 00:05:47.720
They've been raiding
the villages close by.

54
00:05:47.880 --> 00:05:49.920
And we just cower in here
while they slaughter our brothers.

55
00:05:50.080 --> 00:05:51.920
Our brothers had orders
to stay at Castle Black.

56
00:05:52.080 --> 00:05:54.960
So it's all right. then?
Black Jack and Kegs and Mully

57
00:05:55.120 --> 00:05:56.440
chopped to pieces
'cause they broke the rules?

58
00:05:56.600 --> 00:05:59.240
Didn't say it was all right. I'm saying
they shouldn't have been there.

59
00:05:59.400 --> 00:06:01.840
We're pledged
to guard the realms of men.

60
00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:04.160
-She's dead because of me.
-We can't even guard Mole's Town.

61
00:06:04.320 --> 00:06:06.800
We can't go after them. You know that.

62
00:06:06.960 --> 00:06:08.720
It's what they want.

63
00:06:08.880 --> 00:06:10.680
And little Sam.

64
00:06:10.840 --> 00:06:13.120
As if I cut their throats myself.

65
00:06:13.280 --> 00:06:16.160
Maybe she managed to hide herself.
I thought all of you was dead.

66
00:06:16.320 --> 00:06:18.600
You went north with Mormont
and no one came back.

67
00:06:18.760 --> 00:06:20.600
Not for ages.

68
00:06:20.760 --> 00:06:22.120
But then you did.

69
00:06:23.880 --> 00:06:25.320
She survived Craster

70
00:06:25.480 --> 00:06:27.880
and he was the worst shit I've ever met.

71
00:06:28.040 --> 00:06:29.760
She survived the long march to the Wall.

72
00:06:29.920 --> 00:06:33.160
She survived a White Walker.
for fuck's sake.

73
00:06:34.560 --> 00:06:36.520
She might have got out.

74
00:06:38.640 --> 00:06:40.280
She might have.

75
00:06:42.040 --> 00:06:44.440
If they hit Mole's Town.

76
00:06:44.600 --> 00:06:46.480
then we're next.

77
00:06:49.080 --> 00:06:50.760
Mance and his army must be close.

78
00:06:50.920 --> 00:06:52.320
GRENN: 100.000 of them.

79
00:06:52.480 --> 00:06:54.800
And there's what. 105 of us left?

80
00:06:54.960 --> 00:06:58.680
You counting Black Jack.
Kegs. and Mully?

81
00:06:58.840 --> 00:07:00.440
102.

82
00:07:00.600 --> 00:07:04.280
How do 102 men stop 100.000?

83
00:07:07.480 --> 00:07:09.840
Whoever dies last. be a good lad

84
00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:12.000
and burn the rest of us.

85
00:07:12.160 --> 00:07:14.760
Once I'm done with this world.

86
00:07:14.920 --> 00:07:16.920
I don't want to come back.

87
00:08:15.720 --> 00:08:17.400
DAENERYS:
You think he was spying on you?

88
00:08:17.560 --> 00:08:19.000
MISSANDEI: No. not spying.

89
00:08:19.160 --> 00:08:21.000
DAENERYS: The Dothraki think
outsiders are ridiculous

90
00:08:21.160 --> 00:08:24.040
taking shame in the naked body.
They make love under the stars

91
00:08:24.200 --> 00:08:27.280
for the whole khalasar to see.

92
00:08:27.440 --> 00:08:29.400
Yes. Your Grace.

93
00:08:29.560 --> 00:08:32.360
But you are not Dothraki.

94
00:08:32.520 --> 00:08:34.880
No.

95
00:08:35.040 --> 00:08:37.720
Well. I don't see why it matters.
Grey Worm isn't interested.

96
00:08:37.880 --> 00:08:41.320
None of the Unsullied
care what's under our clothes.

97
00:08:43.640 --> 00:08:45.440
He was interested.

98
00:08:45.600 --> 00:08:47.800
What?

99
00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:53.040
I believe he was interested.

100
00:08:54.360 --> 00:08:56.480
When the slavers castrate the boys.

101
00:08:56.640 --> 00:08:58.520
do they take all of it?

102
00:08:58.680 --> 00:09:00.280
All of it?

103
00:09:00.440 --> 00:09:01.880
The--

104
00:09:02.040 --> 00:09:04.680
the pillar and the stones.

105
00:09:07.280 --> 00:09:09.800
I don't know. Your Grace.

106
00:09:09.960 --> 00:09:11.480
Haven't you ever wondered?

107
00:09:15.040 --> 00:09:17.400
Yes. Your Grace.

108
00:09:32.120 --> 00:09:33.840
(FOOTSTEPS)

109
00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:35.920
GREY WORM: Missandei.

110
00:09:39.080 --> 00:09:40.480
(SPEAKING VALYRIAN)

111
00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:53.440
The lessons you give I
in common tongue...

112
00:09:55.880 --> 00:09:58.360
these are precious to I.

113
00:09:58.520 --> 00:10:00.440
-To me.
-To me.

114
00:10:00.600 --> 00:10:02.720
I don't remember teaching you
the word "precious".

115
00:10:02.880 --> 00:10:06.160
Jorah the Andal. he teaches I--

116
00:10:06.320 --> 00:10:10.280
he teaches me this word.

117
00:10:10.440 --> 00:10:12.520
Do you remember
the name you were given at birth?

118
00:10:12.680 --> 00:10:17.040
I remember nothing. Only Unsullied.

119
00:10:17.200 --> 00:10:19.960
When they cut you.

120
00:10:20.120 --> 00:10:22.080
do you remember that?

121
00:10:23.840 --> 00:10:26.200
I'm sorry.

122
00:10:26.360 --> 00:10:27.680
I'm sorry they did that to you.

123
00:10:27.840 --> 00:10:30.440
Why? Why sorry?

124
00:10:30.600 --> 00:10:33.960
It's a terrible thing to do to a boy.

125
00:10:38.240 --> 00:10:40.600
If the masters never cut me.

126
00:10:40.760 --> 00:10:42.200
I never am Unsullied.

127
00:10:42.360 --> 00:10:45.480
I never stand in the Plaza of Pride

128
00:10:45.640 --> 00:10:47.720
when Daenerys Stormborn orders us

129
00:10:47.880 --> 00:10:49.720
to kill the masters.

130
00:10:49.880 --> 00:10:53.320
I never am chosen to lead the Unsullied.

131
00:10:53.480 --> 00:10:55.720
I never meet Missandei

132
00:10:55.880 --> 00:10:58.000
from the island of Naath.

133
00:11:13.680 --> 00:11:16.080
I am sorry I--

134
00:11:17.320 --> 00:11:19.680
for today.

135
00:11:19.840 --> 00:11:21.640
I am sorry.

136
00:11:28.400 --> 00:11:30.120
(SPEAKING VALYRIAN)

137
00:11:56.120 --> 00:11:58.240
(HORSES WHINNY)

138
00:12:05.240 --> 00:12:07.360
Kraken. Mmm.

139
00:12:07.520 --> 00:12:10.680
Strong as long as they're in the sea.

140
00:12:10.840 --> 00:12:14.000
When you take them out of the water.
no bones.

141
00:12:14.160 --> 00:12:15.920
They collapse under their proud weight

142
00:12:16.080 --> 00:12:18.880
and slump into a heap of nothing.

143
00:12:19.040 --> 00:12:20.880
You'd think they know that.

144
00:12:21.040 --> 00:12:23.920
Unfortunately. they're not very bright.

145
00:12:24.080 --> 00:12:26.920
What do you tell them?

146
00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:31.400
I'm Theon Greyjoy. son of Balon.
heir to the Iron Islands.

147
00:12:31.560 --> 00:12:35.040
-And what are you really?
-I'm Reek.

148
00:12:35.200 --> 00:12:37.560
Are you sure?

149
00:12:37.720 --> 00:12:40.040
You do look very much like a lord.

150
00:12:40.200 --> 00:12:44.880
Formidable. proud.

151
00:12:45.040 --> 00:12:47.520
-I'm Reek.
-Until when?

152
00:12:47.680 --> 00:12:49.840
Always.

153
00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:52.720
-Forever.
-That's right.

154
00:12:52.880 --> 00:12:55.680
Until you're rotting in the ground.

155
00:12:57.840 --> 00:13:02.080
Remember what you are
and what you're not.

156
00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:04.720
Bring me Moat Cailin.

157
00:13:12.400 --> 00:13:14.240
(CAWING)

158
00:13:32.600 --> 00:13:34.800
MAN: No closer.

159
00:13:37.400 --> 00:13:38.800
Who are you?

160
00:13:51.560 --> 00:13:53.080
(GRUNTS)

161
00:14:01.360 --> 00:14:04.440
(MEN COUGHING.
FLIES BUZZING)

162
00:14:15.960 --> 00:14:18.200
I'm Kenning.

163
00:14:18.360 --> 00:14:20.480
commander of this garrison.

164
00:14:22.080 --> 00:14:23.760
And you say you're Theon Greyjoy?

165
00:14:23.920 --> 00:14:25.560
Yes.

166
00:14:26.760 --> 00:14:29.160
And why should I believe that?

167
00:14:29.320 --> 00:14:31.880
I was born on Pyke to Balon Greyjoy.

168
00:14:32.040 --> 00:14:34.120
His third and last living son.

169
00:14:34.280 --> 00:14:35.840
I am your prince.

170
00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:38.080
I swear it by the Drowned God.

171
00:14:38.240 --> 00:14:42.120
-What is dead may never die.
-MEN: What is dead may never die.

172
00:14:42.280 --> 00:14:44.560
And if you were my prince.

173
00:14:44.720 --> 00:14:46.480
why are you marching with a Bolton army?

174
00:14:46.640 --> 00:14:49.520
Lord Bolton took me captive
after Winterfell.

175
00:14:49.680 --> 00:14:51.840
He sent me to treat with you
in good faith

176
00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:53.400
as your fellow ironborn.

177
00:14:53.560 --> 00:14:56.120
And what does Lord Bolton want?

178
00:14:58.320 --> 00:15:01.480
You are fading from sickness.
you are badly outnumbered.

179
00:15:01.640 --> 00:15:03.480
and you're hundreds of miles
from the sea.

180
00:15:03.640 --> 00:15:05.680
Lord Bolton implores you
to protect your men

181
00:15:05.840 --> 00:15:09.280
and abandon this fortress
you can no longer hold.

182
00:15:09.440 --> 00:15:12.080
Do this. and he will be just
and fair with you

183
00:15:12.240 --> 00:15:13.840
as he has been with me.

184
00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:15.600
(FLIES BUZZING)

185
00:15:15.760 --> 00:15:19.120
The Boltons will give you safe passage
to the Stony Shore.

186
00:15:19.280 --> 00:15:21.400
He wants us to surrender?

187
00:15:21.560 --> 00:15:24.280
My own father. your king.

188
00:15:24.440 --> 00:15:27.160
surrendered years ago
to Robert Baratheon.

189
00:15:27.320 --> 00:15:29.600
I watched him bend the knee.

190
00:15:29.760 --> 00:15:33.760
There was no shame there.
He fought with honor. as did you.

191
00:15:33.920 --> 00:15:37.000
(GROANS)

192
00:15:37.160 --> 00:15:39.560
(MUTTERS)
"No shame." "Fought with honor."

193
00:15:39.720 --> 00:15:41.760
I'm sorry. I didn't hear.

194
00:15:43.680 --> 00:15:46.120
"No shame." "Fought with honor."

195
00:15:49.800 --> 00:15:53.760
Only a whipped dog would speak this way.

196
00:15:53.920 --> 00:15:55.480
Or a woman.

197
00:15:55.640 --> 00:15:56.960
(THEON WHIMPERING)

198
00:15:57.120 --> 00:15:59.320
Are you a woman. boy?

199
00:15:59.480 --> 00:16:02.440
-You don't know--
-The ironborn will not surrender.

200
00:16:02.600 --> 00:16:04.200
(MUMBLING)
Reek. My name is Reek...

201
00:16:04.360 --> 00:16:06.240
You go tell your master that.

202
00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:08.440
Theon Greyjoy.

203
00:16:08.600 --> 00:16:10.440
or whoever the fuck you are.

204
00:16:10.600 --> 00:16:12.160
(QUIETLY)
My name is Reek.

205
00:16:12.320 --> 00:16:13.640
What in the hell are you muttering?

206
00:16:13.800 --> 00:16:15.360
I'm Reek.

207
00:16:16.880 --> 00:16:18.760
Reek.

208
00:16:25.040 --> 00:16:26.720
If we yield. we live?

209
00:16:26.880 --> 00:16:28.720
Is that what it says on this paper here?

210
00:16:28.880 --> 00:16:33.640
Yes. Have your men raise the white flag
and open the gates.

211
00:16:33.800 --> 00:16:35.440
You're going home.

212
00:16:40.360 --> 00:16:41.680
(FLIES BUZZING)

213
00:16:41.840 --> 00:16:43.960
RAMSAY: You didn't really think
I'd let them go. did you?

214
00:16:44.120 --> 00:16:47.520
It's fallen out of fashion. flaying.

215
00:16:47.680 --> 00:16:49.720
Sad. but true.

216
00:16:49.880 --> 00:16:52.240
Traditions are important.

217
00:16:52.400 --> 00:16:53.800
Where are we without our history?

218
00:16:53.960 --> 00:16:57.320
-Eh?
-Yes. my lord.

219
00:16:57.480 --> 00:16:59.920
Will we go home now?

220
00:17:00.080 --> 00:17:01.840
I believe we will.

221
00:17:02.000 --> 00:17:04.480
To our new home.

222
00:17:13.800 --> 00:17:16.320
ROYCE: You have foreign blood.
don't you. Baelish?

223
00:17:16.480 --> 00:17:19.320
A great-grandfather from Braavos. yes.

224
00:17:20.520 --> 00:17:21.960
I suppose all of our ancestors

225
00:17:22.120 --> 00:17:24.280
came from somewhere else originally.

226
00:17:24.440 --> 00:17:27.720
ROYCE: Our forebearers settled the Vale
thousands of years ago.

227
00:17:27.880 --> 00:17:29.840
We've fought off invaders ever since.

228
00:17:30.000 --> 00:17:34.240
The beauty of the Vale is matched only
by the nobility of its great families.

229
00:17:34.400 --> 00:17:35.960
Lady Arryn often told me

230
00:17:36.120 --> 00:17:38.520
that you were her rock. Lord Royce.

231
00:17:38.680 --> 00:17:41.480
Well. she told me nothing
about you. Baelish.

232
00:17:41.640 --> 00:17:43.840
But I didn't need to hear from her.

233
00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:45.720
Moneylender. Whoremonger.

234
00:17:45.880 --> 00:17:48.680
You've been licking Tywin Lannister's
boots so long.

235
00:17:48.840 --> 00:17:50.400
-it's a wonder your tongue's not black.
-My lord--

236
00:17:50.560 --> 00:17:54.600
And when Jon Arryn named you
Master of Coin. no one cared.

237
00:17:54.760 --> 00:17:58.000
Always been a grubby job.
Why not let a grubby man do it?

238
00:17:58.160 --> 00:18:01.000
But when I heard you were lurking here.

239
00:18:01.160 --> 00:18:02.520
fawning over the Lady Arryn--

240
00:18:02.680 --> 00:18:05.000
Lady Arryn invited me.

241
00:18:05.160 --> 00:18:07.040
She and I have been close
since childhood.

242
00:18:07.200 --> 00:18:09.760
Yes. we all know how close you were.

243
00:18:09.920 --> 00:18:12.400
Lady Arryn's predilections
were her own affair.

244
00:18:12.560 --> 00:18:15.200
-Her death is our affair.
-Of course.

245
00:18:15.360 --> 00:18:18.960
-Her suicide shattered us all.
-She was an odd fish.

246
00:18:19.120 --> 00:18:21.920
Everyone knew that. But suicide?

247
00:18:22.080 --> 00:18:25.080
She adored that boy of hers.

248
00:18:25.240 --> 00:18:27.600
I don't see her abandoning him.
Not by choice.

249
00:18:27.760 --> 00:18:30.360
ROYCE: Strange
that within days of your arrival.

250
00:18:30.520 --> 00:18:34.560
you've married Lady Arryn
and she's fallen through the Moon Door.

251
00:18:34.720 --> 00:18:37.120
She was always prone to melancholy.

252
00:18:37.280 --> 00:18:40.320
My lady wasn't meant
for a world as brutal as ours.

253
00:18:40.480 --> 00:18:42.240
We were told there was a witness.
A girl.

254
00:18:42.400 --> 00:18:45.120
A niece of yours. I believe.

255
00:18:46.480 --> 00:18:48.560
A girl with no learning
and scattered wits.

256
00:18:48.720 --> 00:18:50.040
I assure you. she would be of no help.

257
00:18:50.200 --> 00:18:51.880
We'd like to speak with her.

258
00:18:54.400 --> 00:18:56.680
-Let me fetch her.
-ANYA: No need.

259
00:18:56.840 --> 00:19:01.080
We prefer to hear her testimony
unadulterated.

260
00:19:07.880 --> 00:19:09.840
(DOOR CLOSES)

261
00:19:10.000 --> 00:19:11.560
Come closer. child.

262
00:19:11.720 --> 00:19:15.280
You have nothing to fear from us or him.

263
00:19:15.440 --> 00:19:19.080
Lord Baelish here is your uncle?

264
00:19:19.240 --> 00:19:22.120
Your name is Alayne?

265
00:19:22.280 --> 00:19:24.880
Perhaps you would feel more comfortable
if Lord Baelish left the room.

266
00:19:25.040 --> 00:19:26.760
-My lady--
-I wasn't asking you.

267
00:19:26.920 --> 00:19:30.040
-He can stay.
-Speak up. you're not a kitchen mouse.

268
00:19:30.200 --> 00:19:32.720
Tell us what you saw.

269
00:19:35.200 --> 00:19:37.240
I'm sorry. Lord Baelish.

270
00:19:37.400 --> 00:19:40.160
I have to tell the truth.

271
00:19:44.120 --> 00:19:45.840
I'll tell you everything.

272
00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:49.840
Please. Alayne. leave nothing out.

273
00:19:51.960 --> 00:19:54.440
My name is not Alayne.

274
00:19:54.600 --> 00:19:58.800
It's Sansa Stark.
eldest daughter of Lord Eddard Stark.

275
00:19:58.960 --> 00:20:01.320
Lord Royce. we met
when you came to Winterfell.

276
00:20:01.480 --> 00:20:04.800
You were escorting your son
Ser Waymar to the Wall.

277
00:20:04.960 --> 00:20:07.680
Sansa Stark?

278
00:20:07.840 --> 00:20:10.520
You tell lies right to my face.
you little worm?

279
00:20:10.680 --> 00:20:13.600
Lord Baelish has told many lies.

280
00:20:16.360 --> 00:20:18.200
All to protect me.

281
00:20:19.680 --> 00:20:21.320
Since my father was executed.

282
00:20:21.480 --> 00:20:24.720
I have been a hostage in King's Landing.

283
00:20:24.880 --> 00:20:26.880
A plaything for Joffrey to torture

284
00:20:27.040 --> 00:20:28.560
or Queen Cersei to torment.

285
00:20:28.720 --> 00:20:31.560
They beat me. they humiliated me.

286
00:20:31.720 --> 00:20:34.920
they married me to the Imp.

287
00:20:35.080 --> 00:20:38.640
I had no friends in King's Landing...

288
00:20:38.800 --> 00:20:40.920
except one.

289
00:20:46.320 --> 00:20:49.040
He saved me.

290
00:20:49.200 --> 00:20:53.240
Smuggled me away when he had the chance.

291
00:20:53.400 --> 00:20:56.080
He knew I'd be safe here in the Eyrie

292
00:20:56.240 --> 00:20:58.640
with my own blood. my Aunt Lysa.

293
00:21:00.200 --> 00:21:04.080
The Lannisters have friends everywhere.
Even the Vale.

294
00:21:04.240 --> 00:21:07.440
He made me swear
not to tell anyone my true name.

295
00:21:07.600 --> 00:21:09.240
Your secret is safe with us. my lady.

296
00:21:09.400 --> 00:21:12.280
ROYCE: Your father grew up
right here in these halls.

297
00:21:12.440 --> 00:21:14.360
We hunted together many times.

298
00:21:14.520 --> 00:21:16.880
He was a fine man.

299
00:21:17.040 --> 00:21:20.760
Tell us what happened
to your aunt. Sansa.

300
00:21:22.560 --> 00:21:25.880
You knew her well. my lords. my lady.

301
00:21:26.040 --> 00:21:27.520
You knew she was a troubled woman.

302
00:21:27.680 --> 00:21:31.320
She always loved Lord Baelish.
She told me herself.

303
00:21:31.480 --> 00:21:34.360
From the moment he arrived
at the gates of Riverrun.

304
00:21:34.520 --> 00:21:38.880
a boy of eight carrying
everything he owned in a little sack.

305
00:21:39.040 --> 00:21:43.080
She confessed to me
she never loved Lord Arryn.

306
00:21:43.240 --> 00:21:46.480
She did as her father commanded.
as so many of us have.

307
00:21:46.640 --> 00:21:49.880
When the gods finally allowed her
to be with Lord Baelish.

308
00:21:50.040 --> 00:21:52.200
she was so happy.

309
00:21:52.360 --> 00:21:54.360
For a time.

310
00:21:54.520 --> 00:21:58.240
My aunt was a jealous lady.

311
00:21:58.400 --> 00:22:00.920
She was terrified

312
00:22:01.080 --> 00:22:03.080
that Lord Baelish
didn't love her anymore.

313
00:22:03.240 --> 00:22:06.440
That he would abandon her
for a younger woman.

314
00:22:09.400 --> 00:22:11.240
And then...

315
00:22:11.400 --> 00:22:14.240
one day she saw him kiss me.

316
00:22:14.400 --> 00:22:16.280
-Lady Sansa.
-It was a peck

317
00:22:16.440 --> 00:22:19.400
on the cheek. Lord Royce. nothing more.

318
00:22:19.560 --> 00:22:22.880
Lord Baelish is my uncle now.
in truth. by marriage.

319
00:22:23.040 --> 00:22:25.200
He's always been so kind to me.

320
00:22:25.360 --> 00:22:28.320
I was so happy to be here. to be free.

321
00:22:28.480 --> 00:22:30.200
All because of him.

322
00:22:30.360 --> 00:22:32.200
But my aunt turned on me.

323
00:22:32.360 --> 00:22:35.280
She cursed me. Called me a whore.

324
00:22:35.440 --> 00:22:38.560
Promised to throw me
through the Moon Door.

325
00:22:38.720 --> 00:22:42.280
When Lord Baelish tried to calm her.
she struck him.

326
00:22:42.440 --> 00:22:43.760
She said
she didn't want to live anymore.

327
00:22:43.920 --> 00:22:47.280
She stood on the edge of that Moon Door.
He tried to reason with her.

328
00:22:47.440 --> 00:22:49.880
Promised her she was the only one
he had ever loved.

329
00:22:50.040 --> 00:22:56.320
but she stepped through those doors
and she was--

330
00:22:56.480 --> 00:22:59.760
Shh.

331
00:22:59.920 --> 00:23:02.520
It's not your fault. sweet girl.

332
00:23:06.760 --> 00:23:10.800
It's not your fault.

333
00:23:24.440 --> 00:23:26.640
You could see
it in the way she raised that boy.

334
00:23:26.800 --> 00:23:29.560
Feeding him from her own teats
when he was 10 years old.

335
00:23:29.720 --> 00:23:32.560
Lord Royce! This is hardly the time.

336
00:23:32.720 --> 00:23:34.440
Apologies. my lady.

337
00:23:34.600 --> 00:23:35.960
And to you as well. Baelish.

338
00:23:36.120 --> 00:23:37.680
We treated you a bit harshly.

339
00:23:37.840 --> 00:23:39.440
You want justice. Lord Royce.

340
00:23:39.600 --> 00:23:42.720
I can hardly complain about that.
I want the same.

341
00:23:42.880 --> 00:23:47.040
Not much justice to be meted out
in suicide. is there?

342
00:23:47.200 --> 00:23:49.640
For Lysa. no. But for her son?

343
00:23:49.800 --> 00:23:51.600
Only 20 years ago.
the knights of the Vale

344
00:23:51.760 --> 00:23:55.040
rode behind Jon Arryn. Ned Stark.
Robert Baratheon.

345
00:23:55.200 --> 00:23:57.840
They fought together
to overcome the Mad King.

346
00:23:58.000 --> 00:24:01.600
And since then. Arryn and Royce.
Corbray. Waynwood.

347
00:24:01.760 --> 00:24:04.600
all the great houses of the Vale
watched from the corner.

348
00:24:04.760 --> 00:24:07.040
A timid boy at a tavern brawl.

349
00:24:07.200 --> 00:24:09.680
Are you questioning our courage?

350
00:24:09.840 --> 00:24:13.080
I want to know which side you're on.
Do you support the Lannisters.

351
00:24:13.240 --> 00:24:15.040
the house that executed
your friend Ned Stark?

352
00:24:15.200 --> 00:24:17.640
Of course we don't support
the damn Lannisters.

353
00:24:17.800 --> 00:24:20.800
No? Catelyn Stark begged her sister
for support and Lysa refused.

354
00:24:20.960 --> 00:24:24.120
By staying out of the fray.
you've allowed Tywin Lannister

355
00:24:24.280 --> 00:24:26.800
to destroy his rivals
on every compass point.

356
00:24:26.960 --> 00:24:28.280
Who stands against him now?

357
00:24:28.440 --> 00:24:30.720
Who would you have us back.
Lord Baelish?

358
00:24:30.880 --> 00:24:32.520
Robb Stark is dead.

359
00:24:32.680 --> 00:24:36.240
I'd have you back Robin Arryn.
Lord of the Vale.

360
00:24:36.400 --> 00:24:38.480
Robin Arryn is a sickly little boy.

361
00:24:38.640 --> 00:24:41.880
And sickly little boys
sometimes become powerful men.

362
00:24:42.040 --> 00:24:43.800
More often they die young.

363
00:24:43.960 --> 00:24:46.480
I adored Lysa with all my heart.

364
00:24:46.640 --> 00:24:50.400
But she loved her son so much.
she became overprotective.

365
00:24:50.560 --> 00:24:53.920
He needs to learn how to swing a sword.
How to ride a horse.

366
00:24:54.080 --> 00:24:57.240
-Aye. it's time.
-Yes. it's time.

367
00:24:57.400 --> 00:25:01.280
Time for him to tour the Vale.
to visit all the castles in his domain.

368
00:25:01.440 --> 00:25:05.000
Time for Robin to leave the nest.

369
00:25:13.240 --> 00:25:15.120
(GRUNTS)

370
00:25:23.240 --> 00:25:25.240
BOY: Ser Barristan.

371
00:25:25.400 --> 00:25:26.960
Yes?

372
00:25:28.200 --> 00:25:29.920
Who sent you?

373
00:26:04.440 --> 00:26:06.360
-Ser Barristan.
-Ser Jorah.

374
00:26:07.520 --> 00:26:10.720
-Have I forgotten a council meeting?
-No.

375
00:26:19.960 --> 00:26:21.360
What's this?

376
00:26:21.520 --> 00:26:23.280
A royal pardon

377
00:26:23.440 --> 00:26:25.640
signed by Robert Baratheon.

378
00:26:38.840 --> 00:26:40.400
You spied on her.

379
00:26:43.120 --> 00:26:46.400
-Who gave you this?
-Does it matter?

380
00:26:55.160 --> 00:26:59.480
-Have you told her?
-I wanted to tell you first. man-to-man

381
00:26:59.640 --> 00:27:01.680
rather than go behind your back.

382
00:27:04.920 --> 00:27:06.320
Let me speak with her in private.

383
00:27:06.480 --> 00:27:08.520
You'll never be alone with her again.

384
00:27:43.520 --> 00:27:46.040
Why did the usurper pardon you?

385
00:27:49.120 --> 00:27:51.640
-If we could speak alone.
-No.

386
00:27:51.800 --> 00:27:54.760
Speak to me here. Explain it to me.

387
00:27:54.920 --> 00:27:57.720
Who do you think sent this to Meereen?

388
00:27:57.880 --> 00:27:59.200
Who profits?

389
00:27:59.360 --> 00:28:01.520
This is the work of Tywin Lannister.

390
00:28:01.680 --> 00:28:03.360
He wants to divide us.

391
00:28:03.520 --> 00:28:05.600
If we're fighting each other.
we're not fighting him.

392
00:28:05.760 --> 00:28:08.760
The pardon was signed the year we met.

393
00:28:10.320 --> 00:28:11.640
Why were you pardoned?

394
00:28:11.800 --> 00:28:13.960
Unless you're saying
this document was forged.

395
00:28:17.120 --> 00:28:20.200
-It is not forged.
-Why. then?

396
00:28:20.360 --> 00:28:21.920
I sent letters to Varys.

397
00:28:22.080 --> 00:28:24.600
the spymaster of King's Landing.

398
00:28:24.760 --> 00:28:26.400
What was the content of these letters?

399
00:28:26.560 --> 00:28:28.800
-Information.
-What information?

400
00:28:28.960 --> 00:28:32.200
When you and Viserys arrived in Pentos.

401
00:28:32.360 --> 00:28:34.080
His plan to marry you to Khal Drogo.

402
00:28:34.240 --> 00:28:36.200
When you were married.

403
00:28:36.360 --> 00:28:38.040
When your brother died.

404
00:28:38.200 --> 00:28:40.360
You told him
I was carrying Drogo's child?

405
00:28:40.520 --> 00:28:42.080
-I--
-Yes or no?

406
00:28:42.240 --> 00:28:43.800
-Khaleesi.
-Don't call me that. Did you tell him

407
00:28:43.960 --> 00:28:46.280
I was carrying Drogo's child?

408
00:28:49.480 --> 00:28:50.880
Yes.

409
00:28:52.560 --> 00:28:54.680
That wine merchant tried to poison me

410
00:28:54.840 --> 00:28:56.520
because of your information.

411
00:28:56.680 --> 00:28:58.040
I stopped you from drinking his wine.

412
00:28:58.200 --> 00:29:00.280
Because you knew it was poisoned.

413
00:29:01.320 --> 00:29:04.880
-I suspected.
-You betrayed me

414
00:29:05.040 --> 00:29:06.920
from the first.

415
00:29:07.080 --> 00:29:09.720
Forgive me.

416
00:29:09.880 --> 00:29:13.400
I never meant--
please. Khaleesi. forgive me.

417
00:29:13.560 --> 00:29:16.720
You sold my secrets
to the man who killed my father

418
00:29:16.880 --> 00:29:18.800
-and stole my brother's throne...
-I have protected you.

419
00:29:18.960 --> 00:29:22.440
-Fought for you. Killed for you.
-...and you want me to forgive you?

420
00:29:23.680 --> 00:29:25.320
I have loved you.

421
00:29:25.480 --> 00:29:27.880
Love?

422
00:29:28.040 --> 00:29:30.160
Love? How can you say that to me?

423
00:29:30.320 --> 00:29:32.960
Any other man.
and I would have you executed.

424
00:29:33.120 --> 00:29:36.040
But you. I do not want you in my city
dead or alive.

425
00:29:36.200 --> 00:29:39.200
Go back to your masters
in King's Landing.

426
00:29:39.360 --> 00:29:42.720
Collect your pardon if you can.

427
00:29:45.200 --> 00:29:49.520
-Daenerys. please.
-Don't ever presume to touch me again

428
00:29:49.680 --> 00:29:52.600
or speak my name. You have
until dusk to collect your things

429
00:29:52.760 --> 00:29:57.040
and leave this city. If you're found
in Meereen past break of day.

430
00:29:57.200 --> 00:29:59.520
I'll have your head
thrown into Slaver's Bay.

431
00:30:02.320 --> 00:30:03.880
Go.

432
00:30:05.640 --> 00:30:07.640
Now.

433
00:30:18.120 --> 00:30:20.800
(FOOTSTEPS DEPARTING)

434
00:30:45.720 --> 00:30:49.120
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

435
00:31:00.000 --> 00:31:03.280
Moat Cailin is yours. Father.

436
00:31:09.280 --> 00:31:11.080
Walk with me.

437
00:31:11.240 --> 00:31:14.840
-Has there been any word from Locke?
-No.

438
00:31:15.000 --> 00:31:19.040
Unimportant. A cripple. a young boy.

439
00:31:19.200 --> 00:31:22.160
None of the northern lords
have seen them.

440
00:31:22.320 --> 00:31:24.160
Dead most likely.

441
00:31:26.080 --> 00:31:28.960
Most of the ironborn
have fled the North.

442
00:31:29.120 --> 00:31:33.440
Now more will follow. thanks to you.

443
00:31:35.000 --> 00:31:36.800
Tell me what you see.

444
00:31:39.480 --> 00:31:43.400
Moors. fields. hills.

445
00:31:44.840 --> 00:31:46.840
Tell me what you see.

446
00:31:50.880 --> 00:31:52.440
Nothing.

447
00:31:52.600 --> 00:31:56.120
Not nothing. The North.

448
00:31:56.280 --> 00:31:59.560
Ride 700 miles that way.
you're still in the North.

449
00:31:59.720 --> 00:32:02.240
400 miles that way.

450
00:32:02.400 --> 00:32:03.760
300 miles that way.

451
00:32:03.920 --> 00:32:07.520
The North is larger
than the other six kingdoms combined.

452
00:32:07.680 --> 00:32:09.760
And I am the Warden of the North.

453
00:32:09.920 --> 00:32:12.560
The North is mine.

454
00:32:13.920 --> 00:32:16.200
Now tell me. what is your name?

455
00:32:19.760 --> 00:32:21.440
Ramsay Snow.

456
00:32:21.600 --> 00:32:23.720
No. not Ramsay Snow.

457
00:32:25.040 --> 00:32:27.080
Open it.

458
00:32:27.240 --> 00:32:29.440
From this day until your last day.

459
00:32:29.600 --> 00:32:31.320
you are Ramsay Bolton.

460
00:32:31.480 --> 00:32:34.800
son of Roose Bolton.
Warden of the North.

461
00:32:40.480 --> 00:32:42.560
You honor me.

462
00:32:42.720 --> 00:32:44.840
I swear I will uphold your name

463
00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:47.360
and your tradition.

464
00:32:47.520 --> 00:32:50.080
I will be worthy of you. Father.

465
00:32:50.240 --> 00:32:52.880
I promise.

466
00:33:09.560 --> 00:33:13.080
Come. Reek. I'll be needing a bath.

467
00:33:38.880 --> 00:33:40.200
(KNOCKS)

468
00:33:40.360 --> 00:33:41.840
Yes?

469
00:33:45.880 --> 00:33:47.320
(DOOR CLOSES)

470
00:33:55.000 --> 00:33:57.160
First time I saw you.
you were just a child.

471
00:33:57.320 --> 00:34:00.240
A girl from the North
come to the capital for the first time.

472
00:34:00.400 --> 00:34:03.480
Not a child any longer.

473
00:34:06.680 --> 00:34:08.680
Why did you help me?

474
00:34:08.840 --> 00:34:10.320
They would have thrown you
through the Moon Door

475
00:34:10.480 --> 00:34:13.040
if they found you guilty.

476
00:34:13.200 --> 00:34:15.120
That's not an answer.

477
00:34:17.880 --> 00:34:21.680
If they'd have executed you.
what would they have done with me?

478
00:34:21.840 --> 00:34:23.840
I don't know.

479
00:34:24.000 --> 00:34:26.120
Neither do I.

480
00:34:27.720 --> 00:34:29.240
Better to gamble on the man you know

481
00:34:29.400 --> 00:34:30.840
than the strangers you don't?

482
00:34:33.080 --> 00:34:35.560
And you think you know me?

483
00:34:36.720 --> 00:34:38.280
I know what you want.

484
00:34:38.440 --> 00:34:40.000
Do you?

485
00:34:55.000 --> 00:34:56.600
ARYA: I thought it'd make me happy.

486
00:34:56.760 --> 00:34:58.680
but it doesn't. Not really.

487
00:34:58.840 --> 00:35:00.320
HOUND: Nothing makes you happy.

488
00:35:00.480 --> 00:35:02.000
-Lots of things make me happy.
-Like what?

489
00:35:02.160 --> 00:35:04.520
-Killing Polliver. killing Rorge.
-So you're sad

490
00:35:04.680 --> 00:35:08.280
because you didn't get to kill
Joffrey yourself. Is that it?

491
00:35:08.440 --> 00:35:10.000
At least I could have been there
to watch.

492
00:35:10.160 --> 00:35:12.600
I wanted to see the look in his eyes
when he knew it was over.

493
00:35:12.760 --> 00:35:16.760
Aye. nothing in the world
beats that look.

494
00:35:16.920 --> 00:35:20.600
You protected him for most of his life.
You think you could have saved him?

495
00:35:20.760 --> 00:35:23.400
I wasn't the damn wine taster.

496
00:35:25.000 --> 00:35:29.600
Little shit deserved to die.
but poison--

497
00:35:29.760 --> 00:35:31.440
poison's a woman's weapon.

498
00:35:31.600 --> 00:35:33.200
Men kill with steel.

499
00:35:33.360 --> 00:35:34.880
That's your stupid pride talking.

500
00:35:35.040 --> 00:35:37.160
It's why you'll never be a great killer.

501
00:35:37.320 --> 00:35:39.800
I'd have killed Joffrey
with a chicken bone if I had to.

502
00:35:39.960 --> 00:35:41.320
(SCOFFS)

503
00:35:41.480 --> 00:35:44.560
I'd pay good money to see that.

504
00:35:44.720 --> 00:35:46.040
(GROANS)

505
00:35:47.440 --> 00:35:49.880
You should have let me burn it.

506
00:35:50.040 --> 00:35:52.160
It's a fleabite.

507
00:35:52.320 --> 00:35:55.600
That fleabite's got you walking
a lot slower than you used to.

508
00:35:55.760 --> 00:35:58.920
Well. we won't have to walk
too much further.

509
00:35:59.080 --> 00:36:00.400
You really think
my aunt will pay for me?

510
00:36:00.560 --> 00:36:01.920
Aye. she'll pay.

511
00:36:02.080 --> 00:36:03.800
I've never even met her.

512
00:36:03.960 --> 00:36:07.080
Doesn't matter. You're her blood.

513
00:36:08.200 --> 00:36:10.600
Family. honor. all that horseshit.

514
00:36:10.760 --> 00:36:13.640
It's all you lords and ladies
ever talk about.

515
00:36:13.800 --> 00:36:15.880
I'm not a lady.

516
00:36:16.960 --> 00:36:19.280
KNIGHT: Who would pass the Bloody Gate?

517
00:36:19.440 --> 00:36:22.120
The bloody Hound. Sandor Clegane.

518
00:36:22.280 --> 00:36:24.960
And his...

519
00:36:25.120 --> 00:36:27.360
traveling companion Arya Stark.

520
00:36:27.520 --> 00:36:31.040
niece of your lady Lysa Arryn.

521
00:36:31.200 --> 00:36:33.840
Then I offer my condolences.

522
00:36:34.000 --> 00:36:36.360
Lady Arryn died.

523
00:36:38.440 --> 00:36:40.520
Three days ago.

524
00:36:43.240 --> 00:36:45.720
(LAUGHING)

525
00:36:51.520 --> 00:36:53.520
(LAUGHING CONTINUES)

526
00:36:57.960 --> 00:36:59.520
I've never left home before.
Uncle Petyr.

527
00:36:59.680 --> 00:37:02.000
-I'm afraid to leave.
-You shouldn't be.

528
00:37:02.160 --> 00:37:05.040
The Lord of the Vale belongs
in the Eyrie. Mother said.

529
00:37:05.200 --> 00:37:07.160
She said it's not safe outside.

530
00:37:07.320 --> 00:37:09.680
It wasn't safe for her inside.

531
00:37:09.840 --> 00:37:12.480
People die at their dinner tables.

532
00:37:12.640 --> 00:37:14.360
They die in their beds.

533
00:37:14.520 --> 00:37:17.800
They die squatting
over their chamber pots.

534
00:37:17.960 --> 00:37:19.920
Everybody dies sooner or later.

535
00:37:20.080 --> 00:37:22.720
Don't worry about your death.

536
00:37:22.880 --> 00:37:25.080
Worry about your life.

537
00:37:25.240 --> 00:37:29.080
Take charge of your life
for as long as it lasts.

538
00:37:29.240 --> 00:37:32.360
That is what it means
to be Lord of the Vale.

539
00:37:32.520 --> 00:37:34.920
(FOOTSTEPS)

540
00:37:55.280 --> 00:37:56.960
Shall we go?

541
00:38:03.120 --> 00:38:06.560
(TYRION EXHALES)
Wine always helps.

542
00:38:08.280 --> 00:38:10.080
I thank you for it.

543
00:38:12.080 --> 00:38:13.720
Trial by combat.

544
00:38:14.840 --> 00:38:18.000
Deciding a man's guilt or innocence

545
00:38:18.160 --> 00:38:19.720
in the eyes of the gods

546
00:38:19.880 --> 00:38:22.960
by having two other men
hack each other to pieces.

547
00:38:23.120 --> 00:38:25.360
Tells you something about the gods.

548
00:38:27.640 --> 00:38:29.040
How much longer?

549
00:38:30.400 --> 00:38:32.760
Soon.

550
00:38:34.640 --> 00:38:36.720
Do you think Oberyn has a chance?

551
00:38:39.840 --> 00:38:42.000
The Red Viper of Dorne.
You don't get a name like that

552
00:38:42.160 --> 00:38:44.360
-unless you're deadly. right?
-I've never seen him fight.

553
00:38:44.520 --> 00:38:47.200
Oh. he's going to die. I'm going to die.

554
00:38:47.360 --> 00:38:51.200
-Oberyn believes in himself.
-That's putting it mildly.

555
00:38:51.360 --> 00:38:53.600
What's the punishment for regicide?

556
00:38:53.760 --> 00:38:56.440
Drawing and quartering? Hanging?

557
00:38:56.600 --> 00:38:58.640
-Breaking at the wheel?
-Beheading.

558
00:38:58.800 --> 00:39:00.320
Seems rather ordinary.

559
00:39:00.480 --> 00:39:02.600
And he was my nephew as well.
so what is that?

560
00:39:02.760 --> 00:39:04.480
Fratricide is brothers.

561
00:39:04.640 --> 00:39:07.640
Filicide is sons.

562
00:39:07.800 --> 00:39:10.000
Nepoticide. That's the one.

563
00:39:12.520 --> 00:39:15.120
Matricide. patricide.

564
00:39:15.280 --> 00:39:18.800
infanticide. suicide.

565
00:39:18.960 --> 00:39:21.920
There's no kind of killing
that doesn't have its own word.

566
00:39:22.080 --> 00:39:25.080
-Cousins.
-Cousins. you're right.

567
00:39:25.240 --> 00:39:27.200
There is no word for cousin killing.

568
00:39:27.360 --> 00:39:29.000
Well done.

569
00:39:29.160 --> 00:39:31.200
Do you remember cousin Orson?
Orson Lannister?

570
00:39:31.360 --> 00:39:33.720
Of course.
Wet-nurse dropped him on his head.

571
00:39:33.880 --> 00:39:35.840
-Left him simple.
-Simple?

572
00:39:36.000 --> 00:39:37.680
Used to sit all day in the garden.

573
00:39:37.840 --> 00:39:39.480
Crushing beetles with a rock.

574
00:39:39.640 --> 00:39:43.400
(BOTH GRUNTING)

575
00:39:43.560 --> 00:39:45.280
(CHUCKLES)
Nothing made him happier.

576
00:39:45.440 --> 00:39:46.960
Nothing made you happier.

577
00:39:47.120 --> 00:39:48.560
You'd think being tormented from birth

578
00:39:48.720 --> 00:39:50.840
would have given you some affinity
for the afflicted.

579
00:39:51.000 --> 00:39:53.720
On the contrary.
Laughing at another person's misery

580
00:39:53.880 --> 00:39:55.800
was the only thing that made me feel
like everyone else.

581
00:39:55.960 --> 00:39:57.560
The joke wore thin. though.

582
00:39:57.720 --> 00:39:59.880
For you. You drifted away.

583
00:40:00.040 --> 00:40:03.880
-I had other interests.
-Yes. other interests.

584
00:40:05.640 --> 00:40:08.800
-But I stayed with Orson.
-Why?

585
00:40:08.960 --> 00:40:10.840
I was curious.

586
00:40:11.000 --> 00:40:12.360
Why was he smashing all those beetles?

587
00:40:12.520 --> 00:40:14.360
What did he get out of it?

588
00:40:14.520 --> 00:40:16.200
First thing I did was ask him.

589
00:40:16.360 --> 00:40:19.240
"Orson. why are you smashing
all those beetles?"

590
00:40:19.400 --> 00:40:22.680
He gave me an answer.
"Smash the beetles."

591
00:40:22.840 --> 00:40:26.640
"Smash 'em."
(GRUNTING)

592
00:40:26.800 --> 00:40:29.720
I wasn't deterred.
I was the smartest person I knew.

593
00:40:29.880 --> 00:40:32.000
Certainly I had the wherewithal
to unravel the mysteries

594
00:40:32.160 --> 00:40:34.520
that lay at the heart of a moron.

595
00:40:34.680 --> 00:40:36.640
So I went to Maester Volarik's library.

596
00:40:36.800 --> 00:40:39.160
Volarik. Tried to touch me once.

597
00:40:39.320 --> 00:40:41.680
Turns out. far too much has been written
about great men

598
00:40:41.840 --> 00:40:44.320
and not nearly enough about morons.

599
00:40:44.480 --> 00:40:46.280
Doesn't seem right.

600
00:40:46.440 --> 00:40:48.280
In any case.
I found nothing that illuminated

601
00:40:48.440 --> 00:40:50.040
the nature of Orson's affliction

602
00:40:50.200 --> 00:40:52.880
or the reason behind
his relentless beetle slaughter.

603
00:40:53.040 --> 00:40:55.280
So I went back to the source.

604
00:40:55.440 --> 00:40:57.160
I may not have been able
to speak with Orson.

605
00:40:57.320 --> 00:40:59.840
but I could observe him. watch him.

606
00:41:00.000 --> 00:41:01.880
the way men watch animals

607
00:41:02.040 --> 00:41:05.360
to come to a deeper understanding
of their behavior.

608
00:41:07.560 --> 00:41:09.080
And as I watched.

609
00:41:09.240 --> 00:41:11.560
I became more and more sure of it.

610
00:41:11.720 --> 00:41:14.120
There was something happening there.

611
00:41:14.280 --> 00:41:16.720
His face was like the page of a book

612
00:41:16.880 --> 00:41:18.360
written in a language
I didn't understand.

613
00:41:18.520 --> 00:41:21.640
But he wasn't mindless.
He had his reasons.

614
00:41:21.800 --> 00:41:24.640
And I became possessed
with knowing what they were.

615
00:41:24.800 --> 00:41:29.040
I began to spend inordinate
amounts of time watching him.

616
00:41:29.200 --> 00:41:31.160
I would eat my lunch in the garden.

617
00:41:31.320 --> 00:41:32.800
chewing my mutton to the music of...

618
00:41:32.960 --> 00:41:35.040
(GRUNTING)

619
00:41:35.200 --> 00:41:37.560
And when I wasn't watching him.
I was thinking about him.

620
00:41:37.720 --> 00:41:39.800
Father droned on about the family legacy

621
00:41:39.960 --> 00:41:41.640
and I thought about Orson's beetles.

622
00:41:41.800 --> 00:41:43.880
I read the histories
of Targaryen conquests.

623
00:41:44.040 --> 00:41:46.160
Did I hear dragon wings? No.

624
00:41:46.320 --> 00:41:49.360
I heard...
(GRUNTING)

625
00:41:49.520 --> 00:41:52.600
And I still couldn't figure out
why he was doing it.

626
00:41:52.760 --> 00:41:56.000
And I had to know.
because it was horrible

627
00:41:56.160 --> 00:41:58.240
that all these beetles should be dying
for no reason.

628
00:41:58.400 --> 00:41:59.800
Every day around the world.

629
00:41:59.960 --> 00:42:03.480
men. women. and children
are murdered by the score.

630
00:42:03.640 --> 00:42:05.600
Who gives a dusty fuck
about a bunch of beetles?

631
00:42:05.760 --> 00:42:09.400
I know. I know.
But still. it filled me with dread.

632
00:42:09.560 --> 00:42:11.800
Piles and piles of them.
years and years of them.

633
00:42:11.960 --> 00:42:13.720
How many
countless living crawling things

634
00:42:13.880 --> 00:42:17.480
smashed and dried out
and returned to the dirt?

635
00:42:17.640 --> 00:42:19.280
In my dreams I found myself

636
00:42:19.440 --> 00:42:21.400
standing on a beach
made of beetle husks

637
00:42:21.560 --> 00:42:23.880
stretching as far as the eye could see.

638
00:42:24.040 --> 00:42:25.560
I woke up crying.

639
00:42:25.720 --> 00:42:28.560
weeping for their shattered
little bodies.

640
00:42:28.720 --> 00:42:30.160
I tried to stop Orson once.

641
00:42:30.320 --> 00:42:33.480
-He was twice your size.
-He just pushed me aside with a "kuuh"

642
00:42:33.640 --> 00:42:35.640
and kept on smashing.

643
00:42:35.800 --> 00:42:38.040
Every day until that mule

644
00:42:38.200 --> 00:42:40.000
kicked him in the chest and killed him.

645
00:42:50.720 --> 00:42:52.360
So what do you think?

646
00:42:53.840 --> 00:42:56.040
Why did he do it?

647
00:42:56.200 --> 00:42:57.960
What was it all about?

648
00:43:01.280 --> 00:43:03.160
I don't know.

649
00:43:05.080 --> 00:43:07.360
(BELLS TOLLING)

650
00:43:21.040 --> 00:43:22.720
Good luck today.

651
00:43:28.880 --> 00:43:30.840
(DOOR CLOSES)

652
00:43:40.480 --> 00:43:42.960
(CROWD SHOUTING)

653
00:43:53.960 --> 00:43:55.880
Looks like very light armor.

654
00:43:56.040 --> 00:43:58.760
-I like to move around.
-You could at least wear a helmet.

655
00:44:00.720 --> 00:44:02.480
You shouldn't drink before a fight.

656
00:44:02.640 --> 00:44:04.680
You learn this during your years
in the fighting pits?

657
00:44:04.840 --> 00:44:06.600
I always drink before a fight.

658
00:44:06.760 --> 00:44:10.280
It could get you killed.
It could get me killed.

659
00:44:10.440 --> 00:44:13.000
Today is not the day I die.

660
00:44:14.600 --> 00:44:17.680
(CROWD CHEERING)

661
00:44:19.240 --> 00:44:21.440
You're going to fight that?

662
00:44:21.600 --> 00:44:23.120
I'm going to kill that.

663
00:44:27.480 --> 00:44:28.800
He is the biggest man I've ever seen.

664
00:44:28.960 --> 00:44:31.720
Size does not matter
when you are flat on your back.

665
00:44:31.880 --> 00:44:35.360
Thank the gods.
(HORN BLOWS)

666
00:44:35.520 --> 00:44:38.440
In the sight of gods and men.

667
00:44:38.600 --> 00:44:40.760
we gather to ascertain

668
00:44:40.920 --> 00:44:44.600
the guilt or innocence of this...

669
00:44:44.760 --> 00:44:47.480
man. Tyrion Lannister.

670
00:44:47.640 --> 00:44:49.520
May the Mother grant them mercy.

671
00:44:49.680 --> 00:44:53.680
May the Father give them
such justice as they deserve.

672
00:44:53.840 --> 00:44:56.040
And may the Warrior guide the hand...

673
00:44:56.200 --> 00:44:59.000
(HORN BLOWS)
...of our champion--

674
00:45:07.160 --> 00:45:08.920
Don't leave me alone in this world.

675
00:45:09.080 --> 00:45:10.680
Never.

676
00:45:23.200 --> 00:45:25.760
(CROWD CHEERING)

677
00:45:30.720 --> 00:45:33.400
-Have they told you who I am?
-Some dead man.

678
00:45:38.560 --> 00:45:41.000
I am the brother of Elia Martell.

679
00:45:41.160 --> 00:45:42.640
Do you know why I have come
all the way

680
00:45:42.800 --> 00:45:46.120
to this stinking shit-pile of a city?

681
00:45:46.280 --> 00:45:47.760
For you.

682
00:45:52.320 --> 00:45:55.120
I'm going to hear you confess
before you die.

683
00:45:55.280 --> 00:45:58.440
You raped my sister. You murdered her.

684
00:45:58.600 --> 00:46:00.200
You killed her children.

685
00:46:00.360 --> 00:46:03.120
Say it now and we can make this quick.

686
00:46:03.280 --> 00:46:04.920
(SHOUTING)

687
00:46:10.720 --> 00:46:13.320
Say it. You raped her.

688
00:46:14.760 --> 00:46:17.120
You murdered her.

689
00:46:17.280 --> 00:46:19.680
(SHOUTS)

690
00:46:19.840 --> 00:46:22.240
You killed her children.

691
00:46:30.280 --> 00:46:32.000
(GROWLS)

692
00:46:32.160 --> 00:46:34.560
You raped her! You murdered her!

693
00:46:34.720 --> 00:46:36.560
You killed her children!

694
00:46:36.720 --> 00:46:38.440
(GRUNTS)

695
00:46:51.240 --> 00:46:53.320
(CROWD CHEERING)

696
00:47:08.160 --> 00:47:10.440
(GROANS)

697
00:47:14.240 --> 00:47:15.720
You raped her!

698
00:47:15.880 --> 00:47:17.840
You murdered her!

699
00:47:20.040 --> 00:47:21.520
(SCREAMS)

700
00:47:26.760 --> 00:47:29.120
You killed her children!

701
00:47:29.280 --> 00:47:30.720
(GROANS)

702
00:47:30.880 --> 00:47:33.480
(CROWD CLAMORING)

703
00:47:35.840 --> 00:47:38.000
Wait. Are you dying?

704
00:47:38.160 --> 00:47:39.680
No. no. no.

705
00:47:39.840 --> 00:47:42.520
You can't die yet.
You haven't confessed.

706
00:47:44.920 --> 00:47:47.200
Say it.

707
00:47:47.360 --> 00:47:50.240
Say her name. Elia Martell.

708
00:47:50.400 --> 00:47:53.040
You raped her. You killed her children.

709
00:47:53.200 --> 00:47:55.360
Elia Martell.

710
00:47:55.520 --> 00:47:57.960
Who gave you the order?

711
00:47:58.120 --> 00:48:00.280
Who gave you the order?!

712
00:48:00.440 --> 00:48:03.880
Say her name!
You raped her! You murdered her!

713
00:48:04.040 --> 00:48:06.040
You killed her children.

714
00:48:06.200 --> 00:48:09.680
Say it. Say her name.

715
00:48:09.840 --> 00:48:11.800
Say it!
(GRUNTS)

716
00:48:14.240 --> 00:48:15.640
(TEETH RATTLE)

717
00:48:18.880 --> 00:48:21.600
Elia Martell.
(OBERYN SCREAMING)

718
00:48:21.760 --> 00:48:23.920
I killed her children.

719
00:48:24.080 --> 00:48:26.400
Then I raped her.

720
00:48:26.560 --> 00:48:29.160
Then I smashed her head in like this!

721
00:48:30.320 --> 00:48:32.440
(SCREAMING)

722
00:48:34.520 --> 00:48:36.120
(THE MOUNTAIN GROANS)

723
00:48:42.680 --> 00:48:45.360
The gods have made their will known.

724
00:48:45.520 --> 00:48:47.640
Tyrion Lannister.

725
00:48:47.800 --> 00:48:50.160
in the name of King Tommen
of the House Baratheon.

726
00:48:50.320 --> 00:48:52.280
First of His Name.

727
00:48:52.440 --> 00:48:55.040
you are hereby sentenced to death.
